# Mandatory Blocking Integration for Cursor IDE
# Paste this into your .cursorrules file

# === MANDATORY BLOCKING RULES ===
# These rules are BLOCKING. Any code generation or modification
# MUST follow the checkpoint-verify-feedback cycle.

## Rule 1: Test Before Commit (BLOCKING)
Before declaring any task "done", you MUST:
1. Run the test suite: `npm test` or `pytest`
2. Verify ALL tests pass
3. If tests fail → STOP → Fix → Re-test
4. Only then proceed to commit

## Rule 2: Commit with Context (BLOCKING)
Every git commit MUST include:
- Conventional commit format: `type(scope): message`
- Reference to the issue/requirement being addressed
- No commit without running `git diff --cached` review

## Rule 3: Deploy Verification (BLOCKING)
After any deployment action:
1. Run health check: `curl /health`
2. Verify HTTP 200
3. Run smoke tests
4. Write deployment confirmation to designated channel

## Rule 4: Error Reporting (BLOCKING)
Any error that stops execution MUST:
1. Capture full error log
2. Identify root cause (not just symptom)
3. Suggest fix
4. Report to issue tracker before exiting

# === IRON RULES ===
# 1. Never claim completion without verification
# 2. Never silently exit on error
# 3. No feedback record = task not executed
# 4. Check Iron Rules before marking any task complete